quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  62,9,"O believers! When the call to prayer is made on Friday, then proceed ňĻdiligentlyňļ to the remembrance of Allah and leave off ňĻyourňļ business. That is best for you, if only you knew"
  62,10,"Once the prayer is over, disperse throughout the land and seek the bounty of Allah. And remember Allah often so you may be successful"
  62,11,"When they saw the fanfare along with the caravan, they ňĻalmost allňļ flocked to it, leaving you ňĻO Prophetňļ standing ňĻon the pulpitňļ. Say, ‚ÄúWhat is with Allah is far better than amusement and merchandise. And Allah is the Best Provider.‚ÄĚ"
  63,1,"When the hypocrites come to you ňĻO Prophetňļ, they say, ‚ÄúWe bear witness that you are certainly the Messenger of Allah‚ÄĚ‚ÄĒand surely Allah knows that you are His Messenger‚ÄĒbut Allah bears witness that the hypocrites are truly liars"
  63,2,"They have made their ňĻfalseňļ oaths as a shield, hindering ňĻothersňļ from the Way of Allah. Evil indeed is what they do"
  63,3,"This is because they believed and then abandoned faith. Therefore, their hearts have been sealed, so they do not comprehend"
  63,4,"When you see them, their appearance impresses you. And when they speak, you listen to their ňĻimpressiveňļ speech. But they are ňĻjustňļ like ňĻworthlessňļ planks of wood leaned ňĻagainst a wallňļ. They think every cry is against them. They are the enemy, so beware of them. May Allah condemn them! How can they be deluded ňĻfrom the truthňļ"